*** ARRAY NOTES ****
Array is a data structure that  stores  collection of elements of the same data tupe in 
contiguous memory locations. In contigous memeory here means they are arranged next to each other in
memory. Each element in the array can be accessed directly using its index.

** Key Features of an Array:
1. Data type: All ellements must be of the same data type.
2.Contiguous Memory: All elements are stored in seqeuntial memory locations allowing for
effecient access.
3. Indexing: Each elemet has a unique index, starting at '0' that identifies its position
in th array.
4. Fixed size: Number of elements they cah hold is determined at the  time of declaration.
